lend the shares and get the 2%. They get the dividends but schwab pays be an
equal amount in lieu of dividends. But since that is taxable at regular tax
rates, schwb pays an additional goodwill amount to cover the tax. But the
securities get moved to a new account which is a hassle. And I get a letter of
credit since I lose SIPC protection. I never heard of such a thing. I see no
downside. Any comments?
